A month after the launch of a Sh3 billion road project that will cut across Murang’a and Nyandarua counties, property prices have doubled. 

The 68-kilometre-long Kinyona-Gatura-Njabini road has seen land prices along the route skyrocket as speculators descend on the area. 

While at the end of 2018, an acre in the nearby towns of Gataka-ini, Mwagu, Kiarutara, Kimandi, Ndakaini, Ndunyu ya Chege, Gatunyu, Gatura, Kimakia, Kirwara, Kiunyu and Kihumbu-ini all in Gatanga Sub-County averaged between Sh500,000 and Sh2 million, the price has risen to between Sh1 million and Sh4 million. 



